<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idca913d35-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2429"><num value="2429">§ 2429.</num><heading> Records; audits</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idca913d36-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2429/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A recipient of a loan guarantee shall keep such records and other pertinent documents as the Secretary shall prescribe by regulation, including such records as the Secretary may require to facilitate an effective audit.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idca913d37-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2429/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Access</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary and the Comptroller General of the United States, or their duly authorized representatives, shall have access, for the purpose of audit, to the records and other pertinent documents.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idca913d38-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/451/tII/s210">Pub. L. 109–451, title II, § 210</ref>, <date date="2006-12-22">Dec. 22, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/3360">120 Stat. 3360</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
